Two men were left with moderate to minor injuries after a train crashed into their bakkie at the Klaarwater Train Station, KwaZulu-Natal, on Tuesday morning. Russel Meiring, ER24 spokesperson, said the incident happened just after 8.30 am. He said when paramedics arrived at the scene, they found the bakkie smashed against the side of a passenger train. The two men, believed to be in their 40s, were found walking around their bakkie. Meiring said the men had suffered minor to serious injuries and were taken to hospital. Local authorities were also at the scene for further investigations.